            div(class="col xs12 md6")
                .row.mt30   
                    p Necessity can be expressed to varying degrees in English. The words and phrases used for necessity are:  #[strong must, have to and need. ] 

                div(class="col xs11 col-center")
                    h6.u-textColor_2 “Must” is used when something is necessary or strong recommendation.
                    p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] #[strong e.g. ] You must get a visa before you can travel to the U. K. 
                    p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] #[strong e.g. ] I must see you this evening, the matter is very urgent.
                .row.mt30   
                     

                div(class="col xs11 col-center")
                    h6.u-textColor_2 “Have to” is used when something is necessary but not absolutely necessary.
                    p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] #[strong e.g. ] You have to book a hotel before you travel.
                    p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] #[strong e.g. ] You have to finish your homework tonight. 
                .row.mt30   
                     

                div(class="col xs11 col-center")
                    h6.u-textColor_2 “Need” is also used to express necessity to a lesser extent than “have to”.
                    p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] #[strong e.g. ] I need some help on the project.
                    p #[strong.u-textColor_4 •] #[strong e.g. ] I need to go home early today to collect a package.
                .row.mt30

